CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 9, 1969, pg. 15, reads: "Mt. Ararat Prize Winners - 'Doing Your Thing in Sandbox' was the theme of the recent Baby Contest at Mt. Ararat Baptist Church, and the contestants and their supporters were lavishly entertained in a sidewalk cafe atmosphere, which featured fashions for the small fry. First prize of the baby contest went to Vesta Wilds, daughter of Mr. and Mrs. John Wilds.  Second prize was James Williams, Jr., son of Mr. and Mrs. James Williams.  Other babies in the contest were Cheryl Lynn Black, who placed third, Carmen Beasley, Sharon Atkinson, Mary Kay Chapman, Scott Garland, Constance Newberry, David Southers, and Christopher Popp. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Women holding baby contest winners, including Mrs. John Wilds holding Vesta, Mrs. James Williams holding James Jr., and Eleanor Atkinson holding Sharon on right in second row, in Mt. Ararat Baptist Church
